    "Body": " Senior Accounting Manager at Forte Labs San Francisco, CA ?? About the Job At Forte, we\u2019re building an unprecedented set of easy-to-use tools and services for game developers to integrate blockchain technology into their games, and support thriving community-focused economies. To help ensure the games community at large will benefit from it for years to come, we\u2019re committed to progressively decentralizing our platform so it is free, open, and community-owned. ?? We\u2019ve designed our platform with versatility, flexibility, and interoperability in mind. This allows developers and players to reap the benefits of breakthrough community economics in games that are played, operated, and loved today, while also providing the foundation for the groundbreaking experiences of tomorrow.?? We believe blockchain will enable new economic and creative opportunities for gamers around the world, and have assembled a world-class team of veterans from across the games industry\u2014and a $100M developer fund\u2014to help make it happen. That\u2019s where you come in. ?? ---- As a Senior Accounting Manager, you will play a key role in the company\u2019s accounting department. You will leverage your analytical skills as you partner with our Business Operations, Product, Token Economics, and other teams to provide insightful data and analysis that will drive strategic decisions. You are excited to gain exposure to a wide range of different problem spaces -- spanning technical accounting for crypto assets, operational accounting and financial operations in the blockchain space, and tax planning. You are comfortable diving deep into any task, be it accounting research or financial modeling. Strong candidates possess accounting expertise, exceptional business judgement, and communication skills to deliver consistent, high quality outcomes. Requirements In this role, you will...?? Be responsible for many aspects of accounting, reporting, and compliance, including but not limited to: facilitation of the end-to-end process of financial close, reviewing journal entries and account reconciliations during month end close, collaborating with business owners and Finance functional peers in AP, AR/Revenue, FinOps, Payroll, Tax, FP&A, prepare/review requests from auditors, prepare/review technical accounting memos, among others Assist the team to prepare reports for multiple stakeholders (internal and external), including trend/fluctuation analysis?? Help evaluate, recommend, and implement new financial accounting policies, procedures, financial systems, and controls Be a key member in managing audit, tax, and valuation engagements with third party firms?? Actively partner with other business operations and departments to build scalable processes and drive best practices Provide support to finance management and internal customers as needs arise, including ad-hoc projects Research and implement innovative solutions for operational and technical accounting projects as the company launches blockchain assets. ?? To be a good fit, you have... A \u201croll up the sleeves\u201d attitude that demonstrates a bias towards action and impact Intellectual curiosity and a passion for creative problem-solving with incomplete data Experience in technical accounting research and implementation across various accounting focuses, including revenue recognition and consolidations. Expertise in US GAAP Excellent verbal and written communication skills BA/BS in Accounting, Business, or a related field, and 5-8 years of relevant work experience in accounting. Big 4 accounting firms experience in the US; CPA license preferred Bonus if you also have... Expertise in IFRS Updated knowledge of Emerging Issues Task Force topics on cryptocurrencies Experience with financial modeling, data analysis and visualization?? An understanding of the fundamentals of blockchain technology, developer platforms, game design, and / or token economics. And, if not, a strong desire to learn! Benefits We believe in treating people right to build a great team for the journey ahead. If there\u2019s something important to you that\u2019s not on this list, talk to us! :) Competitive compensation A dynamic startup environment where you will constantly be challenged and exposed to new ideas Macbooks are our standard, but we\u2019re happy to get you whatever equipment helps you get your job done ", 
